        <front>
            <div type="abstract">
                <p tid="1">The collection of dhāraṇī in two subdivisions: 250 <foreign type="term" xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">dhāraṇī</foreign> texts themselves, and a small group of 15 dedication and
                    aspiration prayers (Toh 846–1108).</p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="article">
                <head type="article" tid="3">Dhāraṇī</head>
                <div type="section" xml:id="O1JC114941JC14717-article-1">
                    <milestone unit="chunk" xml:id="O1JC114941JC14717-1"/>
                    <p tid="7">This broad section of Dhāraṇī, which corresponds to the <title xml:lang="Bo-Ltn">gzungs ’dus</title> division of the Degé Kangyur, contains two subdivisions: the
                        Compendium of Dhāraṇīs, a collection of 249 <foreign type="term" xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">dhāraṇī</foreign> texts themselves (Toh 846-1093), and a small group of 15 texts (Toh
                        1094-1108) included at the end of the section as a whole by way of dedication and aspiration prayers.</p>
                    <milestone unit="chunk" xml:id="O1JC114941JC14717-2"/>
                    <p tid="8">For more detailed descriptions of the two subsections, see the knowledge base articles <ref target="/knowledgebase/compendium-dharanis.html">Compendium of Dhāraṇīs (Kangyur Section)</ref> and <ref target="/knowledgebase/aspiration.html">Aspiration (Kangyur Section)</ref>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
